FuncDef: This command can be used to override specific attributes of the specified queue s CBS parameters.

ParaDef.Info: The size parameter is an integer expression of the number of kilobytes reserved for the queue. If a value of 10KBytes is wanted, enter the value 10. A value of 0 specifies that no reserved buffers are required by the queue (a minimal reserved size can still be applied for scheduling purposes). Values-0 to 131072, default.
